estate. We should remember that security in Westminster is everyone’s responsibility.     Share         Business Before Questions       University of London Bill [ Lords ] (By Order)            Second Reading opposed and deferred until Tuesday 16 October at Four o’clock (Standing Order No. 20 ).          Oral Answers to Questions     Justice       The Secretary of State was asked—          Bailiffs      The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Yvonne Fovargue (Makerfield) (Lab)       Share       1. What assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of the regulation of bailiffs.  [906985]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Justice (Lucy Frazer)       Share       Mr Speaker, may I share in your remarks about PC Palmer and pay tribute to him and his work in this House? As chair of the all-party parliamentary group on debt and personal finance, the hon. Member for Makerfield (Yvonne Fovargue) is campaigning hard on this important issue, and she is right that bailiffs are not operating as they should in some areas. I was pleased to have the opportunity to meet with the hon. Member for Croydon Central (Sarah Jones) and her constituents, the Rogers family, who sadly lost Jerome as a result of and following some action by bailiffs. We intend to launch a call for evidence shortly to evaluate our most recent bailiff reforms.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Yvonne Fovargue       Share       I, too, met the family of Jerome Rogers, and I pay tribute to them for their courage in taking the campaign forward. However, Jerome’s case perfectly highlights why the industry ne